result.name: Hoi Kee Walnut Place

reviews.text: A very popular sweetsoup shop. A fusion of Chinese and Western dessert. Worth trying but spare more time to queue.
Best walnut dessert in Prince Edward! It has  crunchy bits in make the texture more outstanding

very good tong shui at hoi kee as always 

all 3 dessert were good, and can be served hot or cold..

I like my hot walnut paste with almond paste best. they are very smooth and not too sweet, just what they should be👍

the 2 cold ones were ok..but the tau huay bean curd added nothing for me i can do without..& for that combination i prefer snow fungus with lotus seeds

27.5.2019

Our palate is educated by real Hong Kong style desserts. Two dessert houses of the same brand only 50 meters apart on the same street.  Very popular and get crowded starting at 8 pm. We only ordered hot desserts and absolutely no disappointment.  Everyone is happy after the sugary treat!
Dessert chinese style moderne

result.formatted_address: 香港太子西洋菜南街232號
result.name: 海記合桃坊甜品

reviews.text: 最喜歡的ㄧ間甜品店😋有很多款式中式嘅糊類已及ㄧ些新式特别的配搭也做得不錯!
食物無傳聞般好味，要等好耐先有坐位，又要等好耐先等到食物。坐位細到似幼稚園小朋友櫈仔。
劣食，芋圓係急凍無味色素芋圓，榴槤既甜品完全無榴槤味……
甜品一貫的好!且店員對老人家亦服務周到!怕老人家在門外等位站得久了，細心地遞上圓凳，坐一下吧；老人家要去洗手間，店員們亦保持笑容，提醒地滑呵…總之，服務好，甜品美味!
A very popular sweetsoup shop. A fusion of Chinese and Western dessert. Worth trying but spare more time to queue.
